The paper analyzes publication practices in computer science, specifically in the ACM Digital Library, and focuses on subdisciplines captured by ACM's Special Interest Groups (SIGs). This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the categories of Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Computers and Society (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
